diff --git a/ms-text-structured-encoding-README.md b/ms-text-structured-encoding-README.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..2ade26aa
--- /dev/null
+++ b/ms-text-structured-encoding-README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,51 @@
+# Testing Mooneer's structured EOO callsign encoding
+
+This branch exists purely to make it quick to re-test Mooneer's WIP
+callsign-encoding work whenever he wants more data. See GitHub issue
+https://github.com/drowe67/freedv-gui/issues/1423 and
+https://github.com/tmiw/freedv-backend/pull/22 (WIP, DO NOT MERGE) for
+background.
+
+**Do not merge this branch or open a PR from it.** It points the build at
+someone else's unmerged experimental branch, which breaks EOO callsign
+interop with any station not running the same backend (confirmed on-air
+2026-07-08 — see project_callsign_slash_eoo_fix.md memory / issue #1423
+comments for details).
+
+## What's in this branch
+
+- `cmake/BuildFreeDVBackend.cmake`: `GIT_TAG` changed from `main` to
+  `ms-text-structured-encoding` (tmiw/freedv-backend). This is the only
+  functional change — it just controls which branch of the RADE backend
+  gets fetched and compiled.
+- `ms-text-structured-encoding-extra-tests.patch`: a patch (against
+  `tmiw/freedv-backend`, NOT this repo) that adds issue-#1423 real-world
+  callsigns to `RadeTextUnitTest.cpp`'s test 7, plus a diagnostic printf
+  showing what actually got decoded on failure. The fetched backend source
+  lives outside of this repo's git tree (`build_linux/_deps/freedv_backend-src/`),
+  so this patch is the only record of those additions.
+
+## How to re-test
+
+```
+# 1. Build normally from this branch — CMake will fetch tmiw's branch.
+cmake -S . -B build_linux -DBUILD_BACKEND_UNITTESTS=ON
+cmake --build build_linux -j$(nproc)
+
+# 2. Apply the extra test cases to the fetched backend source, then rebuild
+#    just the test target:
+cd build_linux/_deps/freedv_backend-src
+git apply /path/to/ms-text-structured-encoding-extra-tests.patch
+cd -
+cmake --build build_linux --target RadeTextUnitTest -j$(nproc)
+
+# 3. Run it — fully offline, no RF/radio involved:
+./build_linux/_deps/freedv_backend-build/src/pipeline/RadeTextUnitTest
+```
+
+Known result as of 2026-07-08: `/` collision is fixed; short compound calls
+(`K6AQ/5`, `VK/K6AQ`, `VP8/G4ABC`, `JA1ABC/MM`, `OE/MW0CQU/P`) round-trip
+correctly. `EA7/G9ZZZ` and `3DA0/VK6AQ` still fail — the routing-prefix
+parser rejects a trailing call-area digit that the base-callsign parser
+already handles. Reported to Mooneer:
+https://github.com/drowe67/freedv-gui/issues/1423#issuecomment-4919100750
